name: glyceraldehyde-3-phosphate dehydrogenase (phosphorylating)
classes: Acting on the aldehyde or oxo group of donors;
With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
reaction: D-glyceraldehyde 3-phosphate + phosphate + NAD+ = 3-phospho-D-glyceroyl phosphate + NADH + H+ [RN:R01061]
comment: Also acts very slowly on D-glyceraldehyde and some other aldehydes; thiols can replace phosphate.
